, Somme, Picardie, France":"Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France","Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Amiens","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English:  see  Ames  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ames","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Old French personal name <i>Amis</i> or from the feminine form, <i>Amice</i>. The Old French word <i>amis</i>, is from Latin <i>amicus</i> ‘friend’, which was used in Late Latin as a term for a man of the lower classes, in particular a slave. There were also derivatives of this as personal names, in particular masculine <i>Amicius</i> and feminine <i>Amicia</i>. Both were in use as personal names in England and may have contributed to the surname.","German: perhaps a nickname for an active person, from an ancient Germanic word related to Old High German <i>amazzig</i> ‘busy’.","Dutch: possibly a patronymic from <i>Ame</i> a common personal name in Holland and Friesland, an abbreviated form of an ancient Germanic personal name, perhaps beginning with <i>amel</i> ‘strong’."]}]},{"name":"Gilles","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Aegidus</i>, Old French <i>Gide</i>.  See  <b>Giles</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gilles D' Amiens was born in 1250, in Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France, his father, Pierre d’Amiens, was 35 and his mother, Aelis De Senarpont, was 25. He married Anne Gersende de Conty on 14 February 1272, in Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1284, in his hometown, at the age of 34."},"et":{"1250–1284":"1250–1284","1252–1296":"1252–1296","1278–1323":"1278–1323","1215–1279":"1215–1279","1225–1259":"1225–125